    "body": "Anyway, I see the bug now. What seems to happen is that the first `wait` reads from the `done` channel and stores the discovered `nat.Interface` in `n.found`. The second (concurrent) `wait` checks before it is stored and waits on the channel as well. We can probably just put the lock around the whole thing instead of taking it twice. Or use `sync.Once`.\n",
